    "body": "On bleeding edge.\r\n\r\nPreparation:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt grdcut -RNO -Gno.nc @earth_relief_10m\r\ngmt grdcut -RIS -GIS.nc @earth_relief_02m\r\n```\r\n\r\nForget ``-R`` and gmt complains about missing ``-I``:\r\n```\r\n$ gmt grdblend no.nc is.nc -I1m\r\ngrdblend [WARNING]: Must specify -I if input grids have different increments\r\n```\r\n\r\nNo point in blending one grid, but:\r\n```\r\n$ gmt grdblend no.nc -I1m -RNO\r\ngrdblend [ERROR]: NetCDF variable lat has different dimension (139) from others (257)\r\ngrdblend [WARNING]: Long input record (4585 bytes) was truncated to first 4094 bytes!\r\ngrdblend [ERROR]: Cannot find file \ufffdHDF\r\ngrdblend [ERROR]: Cannot find file \ufffdHDF\r\ngrdblend [ERROR]: File \ufffdHDF not found\r\n[Session gmt (0)]: Error returned from GMT API: GMT_FILE_NOT_FOUND (16)\r\n```\r\n\r\nCalls to ``grdsample`` for resampling causes crash:\r\n```\r\n$ gmt grdblend no.nc is.nc -I1m -RIS\r\ngrdblend [WARNING]: File no.nc entirely outside longitude range of final grid region (skipped)\r\ngrdblend [WARNING]: File is.nc has different increments (0.0833333333333/0.0833333333333) than the output grid (0.0166677360483/0.0166346142132) - must resample\r\ngrdblend [WARNING]: File is.nc coordinates are phase-shifted w.r.t. the output grid - must resample\r\nERROR: Caught signal number 11 (Segmentation fault) at\r\n/usr/local/lib/libgmt.so.6(gmt_grd_get_format+0x62)[0x7fddbbe16752]\r\n[0x0]\r\nStack backtrace:\r\n/usr/local/lib/libgmt.so.6(sig_handler+0x26e)[0x7fddbbdac24e]\r\n/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpthread.so.0(+0x12730)[0x7fddbb84f730]\r\n/usr/local/lib/libgmt.so.6(gmt_grd_get_format+0x62)[0x7fddbbe16752]\r\n/usr/local/lib/libgmt.so.6(GMT_grdblend+0x38d)[0x7fddbbffed7d]\r\n/usr/local/lib/libgmt.so.6(GMT_Call_Module+0x3ee)[0x7fddbbdca24e]\r\ngmt(main+0x260)[0x55d3999a8430]\r\n/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6(__libc_start_main+0xeb)[0x7fddb934009b]\r\ngmt(_start+0x2a)[0x55d3999a94aa]\r\n```",
