            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Well, so when **grdblend** is given a _single_ input file it assumes you are giving it an ascii blend file, since giving it a single grid is meaningless (what is there to blend).  So the messages has to do with wrong reading paths.\r\nI will see if we can protect against this situation by checking if the input file is a grid and then give an error.\r\n",
